HEADWORD: Bitter spar
<hw>Bit"ter spar"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <def>A common name of dolomite;
-- so called because it contains magnesia, the soluble salts of which
are bitter. See <er>Dolomite</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bittersweet</ent>⟦br⟧
